    {
      "id": "1774267632941-o4536lz",
      "publicationId": "alice-in-wonderland",
      "type": "note",
      "locator": {
        "href": "OEBPS/2161886177641920366_11-h-2.htm.html",
        "type": "application/xhtml+xml",
        "locations": {
          "progression": 0,
          "position": 10,
          "totalProgression": 0.10714285714285714
        },
        "text": {
          "highlight": "“Curiouser and curiouser!” cried Alice (she was so much surprised, that for the moment she quite forgot how to speak good English); “now I’m opening out like the largest telescope that ever was! Good-bye, feet!” (for when she looked down at her feet, they seemed to be almost out of sight, they were getting so far off)."
        }
      },
      "color": "blue",
      "note": "Adda note in blue",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-23T12:07:12.941Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-23T12:07:12.941Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "1774267669781-0q1eowf",
      "publicationId": "alice-in-wonderland",
      "type": "note",
      "locator": {
        "href": "OEBPS/2161886177641920366_11-h-2.htm.html",
        "type": "application/xhtml+xml",
        "locations": {
          "progression": 0,
          "position": 10,
          "totalProgression": 0.10714285714285714
        },
        "text": {
          "highlight": "And she went on planning to herself how she would manage it. “They must go by the carrier,” she thought; “and how funny it’ll seem, sending presents to one’s own feet! And how odd the directions will look!"
        }
      },
